            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The codeblock highlighting on the site does not match the site theme. In particular it has purple which is nowhere else in the site theme.\n\nI've just had a thought to suggest a darker background for code blocks, but with the same hue. But after looking at colors, it already is:\n- Basic background is `#0f191f`, which is [lightness 11, chroma 2, hue 235](https://bottosson.github.io/misc/colorpicker/#0f191f).\n- Codeblock background is `#0b151b`, which is [lightness 9, same chroma (2) and hue (235)](https://bottosson.github.io/misc/colorpicker/#0b151b).\n\nSo although they might not look like coordinated, they are. Maybe going even more dark will be an improvement? Here is what `#040d12` (lightness 6, chroma 2, hue 235) looks like as code background:\n\n<img width=\"2153\" height=\"1608\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1578bf8d-e43e-4b14-b0cd-61d97ed4fceb\" />\n\nThis makes code blocks stand out more and (as a bonus) improves contrast ratio in them.",
