            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The main goal here is to not use purple, the syntax should align with the site theme. Your screenshots still have purple.\n\nAh, you mean foreground in syntax highlighting... 🤦 I thought you meant background of codeblocks.\n\nYeah, I agree. Not huge issue for me, but might be not very well aligned.\n\nAs far as I can tell from the place of the screenshot, the color is `#c0caf5`. Which means that it comes from [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/blob/a8f484941f3212b3a370fc8a3aab613c25109a46/css/neovim-hi.css#L44). And [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/blob/a8f484941f3212b3a370fc8a3aab613c25109a46/css/neovim-hi.css#L49) is the only place that uses it.\n\nIf `--hi-b-white` is replaced with site's default foreground (`#a9d5c4`), here is how it looks:\n\n<img width=\"2135\" height=\"1600\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93e75ef9-a402-49a7-8ce2-0258001a1349\" />\n\nThe comments are darker purple also. If `--hi-white` is also replaced with link's color (`#5fb950`), here is how it looks:\n\n<img width=\"2377\" height=\"1343\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d89c036c-fb7c-4809-9f72-98c023643ea8\" />\n\nMaybe a bit too much green, but no purple at least :)\n\n---\n\nFor reference, the theme came in #303 and #304",
